20/12/2009
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Ali Ahmeti, leader of the Democratic Union for Integration (DUI), was re-elected on Saturday (December 19th). 
He was the only candidate for the post. 
In his victory speech, Ahmeti expressed hope that during Spain's EU presidency, which starts on January 1st, the long-standing name dispute between Macedonia and Greece will be resolved and Macedonia "will finally become a member of NATO and will start talks on full-fledged EU membership." (A1, Dnevnik - 19/12/09)
